---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import Signoff from '@/components/Signoff.astro'
---

<BaseLayout>
  <div>
    <div class="project-wrapper">
      <div>
        <div
          class="prose prose-lg md:prose-xl bg-background shadow-md rounded my-5 p-5 max-w-none"
        >
          <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl title text-center mb-8">
            Hi, I'm Lindsay Wardell
          </h1>
          <img
            src="/lindsay2.jpg"
            alt=""
            class="w-[300px] rounded-lg shadow-md md:float-right md:m-4 m-auto"
          />
          <p>
            I'm a programmer and writer. I've been working in software since
            2015, and I currently work as a Senior Software Engineer at <a
              class="underline"
              href="https://mangomint.com">Mangomint</a
            >. I've worked on projects for individuals and small businesses as
            well as large organizations. I love talking to people about what
            they do, what they care about, and what their experiences have been
            like.
          </p>
          <p>
            Writing has always been a passion of mine. In elementary school I
            wrote the heartfelt epic of "The Adventures of Jake" as he quested
            around the world fighting bad guys and collecting the chaos emeralds
            (I was a big fan of Sonic the Hedgehog). In middle school I turned
            to drawing comics (again Sonic themed) and started writing stories
            for tabletop roleplaying games. In high school I discovered a joy
            for worldbuilding, and started writing my first novel (which has
            been regrettably misplaced).
          </p>
          <p>
            As a young adult, I kept coming back to writing fiction, and later
            poetry, as a way to explore what I was feeling and seeing around me.
            Creative expression is something I'm always searching for (I also
            love singing and playing viola), but in writing I felt like I found
            a voice and flow. I could create a world, a story, a set of rules.
            Today, I continue to explore those worlds, drawing them and telling
            their stories. I'm currently working on a fantasy novel, which I
            hope to share with the world some time in the next year or so.
          </p>
          <p>
            Professionally, I've worked on a number of projects ranging from a
            corporate application to a 5-person startup. I've used common tools
            (like React or Ruby on Rails) as well as less known ones (such as
            Elm or Haskell). Personally, I enjoy working with a functional
            programming lens, because I find it helps me organize what I am
            doing, but I appreciate the power in object-oriented languages like
            Kotlin and C#.
          </p>
          <a
            href="/resume"
            class="not-prose block w-1/2 min-w-[250px] mx-auto text-center rounded-lg border border-accent/30 hover:border-accent/60 transition-colors p-4 mt-8 no-underline"
          >
            <p class="text-lg font-title">Want to work together?</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-muted mt-1">Check out my resume &rarr;</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="px-8">
        <Signoff hideIntro />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
